list_ex_of_english: I am distressed that craft training units—for welders and engineers, for instance—are being closing down and business schools opened in their place.
There are 13 men unemployed for every one vacancy for welders.
Riveters, welders and electricians are needed, but not joiners, carpenters or furnishing tradesmen.
Thirdly, male roles that demanded qualifications, such as welder, carpenter and so on, were better-paid than female ones (as packers, cleaners).
I am referring to people such as civil servants and welders.
I told them of a yard which badly needed electric welders, and could not get them.
The present publicly owned responsible industry has welders available to deal with any leakage.
It includes fitting trades, shipwrights, boilermakers, coppersmiths, plumbers, joiners, carpenters, pattern makers, welders, instrument makers, sail makers, printers and lithographers.
